%I A309412 #17 May 24 2026 19:10:13
%S A309412 103,157,37159
%N A309412 Numbers k such that (45^k + 1)/46 is prime.
%C A309412 Larger terms correspond to probable primes.
%H A309412 P. Bourdelais, <a href="https://listserv.nodak.edu/cgi-bin/wa.exe?A2=NMBRTHRY;417ab0d6.0906">A Generalized Repunit Conjecture</a>.
%H A309412 OEIS Wiki, <a href="https://oeis.org/wiki/Primes_of_the_form_(a%5En%2Bb%5En)/(a%2Bb)_and_(a%5En-b%5En)/(a-b)">Primes of the form (a^n+b^n)/(a+b) and (a^n-b^n)/(a-b)</a>.
%t A309412 Do[p=Prime[n]; If[PrimeQ[(45^p + 1)/46], Print[p]], {n, 1, 1000000}]
%o A309412 (PARI) is(n)=ispseudoprime((45^n+1)/46)
%K A309412 nonn,bref,hard,more,changed
%O A309412 1,1
%A A309412 _Paul Bourdelais_, Jul 29 2019
